post_text: Kenston is hosting the Frank Gibas Invitational cross country tournament this Saturday September 5th. There will be 17 other high schools at Kenston for this meet. We are in need of volunteers for different areas of the meet. Whether it is an hour or 4, any time you can give would be great. You can volunteer with your high schooler and help them get a few volunteer hours as well. Everything is done by noon. If you are able to help with this awesome event, please email Laura Fisher at thefishers@windstream.net. Thank you!

post_text:
Saturday, August 31st is the 1st Annual Kenston Invitational. There will be a dedication to Coach Frank Gibas at 8:30 am followed by 4 races, all finishing before noon. Please come out and share in the festivities.

Interested in helping out? We could use a lot of volunteers to make the invitational run smoothly. Please contact David Fisher dfisher@custommaterials.com or Chris Ickes christopherickes@gmail.com to let them know they can count on you.

The course will be a top notch course incorporating the trails, the track and the wind turbine. It will be very spectator friendly. Bring out the whole family!

Hope to see you Saturday.

post_text:
Christopher Ickes

Alumni, we are putting together an awesome video montage for Gibas to celebrate his legacy as a coach and the 30th anniversary of the State Championship team. Can you help?

Please record a 10 second max video of you talking about Coach Gibas. Share anything - a memory, a saying, some way he helped, something funny, anything. Then email that 10 second video to christopherickes@gmail.com & alumni@kenstonlocal.org. Please, do it today and send it to us now so we can put it all together.

We will present the video to Gibas on Saturday, August 31st at 8:30 am as we unveil the new http://kenstonfitnesstrails.com/ at the Frank Gibas Invitational.
